WEBVTT

00:03.086 --> 00:07.589
PlCARD:
Captain's log, stardate 42625.4.

00:07.757 --> 00:09.967
We are entering orbit
around the eighth planet

00:10.135 --> 00:14.263
in this previously unmapped
Theta One-Sixteen solar system.

00:14.431 --> 00:16.181
We diverted
from our scheduled course

00:16.349 --> 00:18.100
when a passing Klingon cruiser

00:18.268 --> 00:21.061
reported discovering pieces
of a strange vessel

00:21.229 --> 00:23.772
in the upper atmosphere
of this planet.

00:23.940 --> 00:25.941
We have come to investigate.

00:26.109 --> 00:27.443
Nasty.

00:27.610 --> 00:31.238
Nitrogen, methane, liquid neon.

00:31.406 --> 00:35.075
Surface temperature
minus 291 degrees Celsius.

00:35.243 --> 00:39.329
Winds up to 31 2 meters
per second.

00:39.497 --> 00:41.123
Not exactly a vacation planet, huh?

00:41.291 --> 00:44.626
Heh. Uh-uh. Not unless
you like ammonia tornadoes.

00:45.462 --> 00:49.465
But l have found indications
of debris in an elliptical orbit.

00:49.632 --> 00:50.716
RlKER:
You keep me informed.

00:50.884 --> 00:53.052
The sooner we find out
what the Klingons think they saw

00:53.219 --> 00:54.887
the sooner we can get
the hell out of here.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.889
Sounds good to me.

01:00.894 --> 01:02.478
Nasty.

01:02.687 --> 01:03.729
[DOOR CHlMES]

01:03.897 --> 01:05.439
Come.

01:09.861 --> 01:12.946
Fermat's last theorem.
You're familiar with it?

01:13.114 --> 01:14.490
Vaguely.

01:14.657 --> 01:16.241
l spent too many math classes
daydreaming

01:16.409 --> 01:18.410
- about being on a starship.
- Mm.

01:19.079 --> 01:20.496
When Pierre de Fermat died,

01:20.663 --> 01:24.416
they found this equation scrawled
in the margin of his notes.

01:24.584 --> 01:28.587
X to the nth plus Y to the nth equals Z
to the nth where N is greater than two,

01:28.755 --> 01:31.173
which he said had no solution
in whole numbers.

01:31.341 --> 01:36.345
But he also added this phrase,
"remarkable proof."

01:36.513 --> 01:39.431
Yeah, that's starting to come back
to me. There was no proof included.

01:39.599 --> 01:43.519
Mm-hm. And for 800 years,
people have been trying to solve it.

01:43.686 --> 01:46.438
- lncluding you.
- l find it stimulating.

01:46.606 --> 01:49.441
Also, it puts things into perspective.

01:49.609 --> 01:53.153
ln our arrogance,
we feel we are so advanced

01:53.321 --> 01:55.739
and yet we cannot unravel
a simple knot

01:55.907 --> 01:58.826
tied by a part-time
French mathematician,

01:58.993 --> 02:01.912
working alone, without a computer.

02:03.248 --> 02:06.333
Captain, we've detected
some sort of debris in a loose orbit.

02:06.501 --> 02:08.085
- Can you identify it?
- No, sir.

02:08.253 --> 02:10.379
l suggest we beam a section aboard
for analysis.

02:10.547 --> 02:12.673
Make it so, Number One.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.144
We've locked onto something
with markings on it.

02:25.311 --> 02:28.939
- What sort of markings?
- Uncertain. Energize.

02:53.464 --> 02:56.216
We've got ourselves a little puzzle,
Number One.

02:56.384 --> 02:58.927
Yes, sir, l guess we have.

03:25.288 --> 03:29.333
PlCARD:
Space, the final frontier.

03:29.959 --> 03:33.962
These are the voyages
ofthe starship Enterprise.

03:34.130 --> 03:39.134
lts continuing mission:
to explore strange new worlds,

03:39.928 --> 03:44.348
to seek out new life
and new civilizations,

03:44.515 --> 03:48.727
to boldly go where no one
has gone before.

04:49.038 --> 04:52.874
Analysis bears out that the object
was definitely terrestrial in origin,

04:53.042 --> 04:55.794
- dated mid-21 st century.
- No, no.

04:55.962 --> 04:59.631
No Earth ship of that time
could have traveled out this far.

04:59.799 --> 05:02.009
Nevertheless,
that is what our tests indicate.

05:02.176 --> 05:05.637
And the markings we discovered
are consistent with this hypothesis.

05:05.805 --> 05:08.265
Any indication of what destroyed it,
Data?

05:08.933 --> 05:11.768
That is even more significant
than the object itself, counselor.

05:11.936 --> 05:13.270
On several of its surfaces,

05:13.438 --> 05:15.647
the molecules seem
to have disintegrated.

05:16.149 --> 05:17.649
Disintegrated? How?

05:18.192 --> 05:21.570
Almost as if they were hit
by a weapon from our time.

05:22.071 --> 05:24.489
Curiouser and curiouser.

05:24.657 --> 05:25.699
WESLEY [OVER COM]:
Captain,

05:25.867 --> 05:28.827
we've detected a large
structure on the planet.

05:32.415 --> 05:33.999
WESLEY:
lt's a building of some sort.

05:34.167 --> 05:36.793
Situated on a plane
of frozen methane,

05:36.961 --> 05:39.796
smack in the middle
of a tremendous storm belt.

05:39.964 --> 05:42.966
l don't believe this. That structure
is surrounded with breathable air.

05:43.134 --> 05:44.926
ls there any connection
between that structure

05:45.094 --> 05:46.595
and the ship fragment
that we found?

05:46.763 --> 05:48.597
Unknown, sir.

05:49.265 --> 05:51.266
- Suggestions?
- Just one, sir.

05:51.434 --> 05:53.268
We could go down there
and have a look.

05:53.436 --> 05:56.438
Breathable air, no life-forms.
That might be dangerous.

05:56.606 --> 06:00.317
l think we could risk a minimal
away team, Number One.

06:02.278 --> 06:03.320
Give me a moment, gents.

06:03.488 --> 06:06.365
We're dealing
with an extremely narrow access point.

06:08.409 --> 06:10.619
Phasers on stun.

06:12.497 --> 06:13.955
Ready when you are.

06:14.624 --> 06:16.458
l believe we've got it now.

06:16.626 --> 06:19.378
- You have a green light, commander.
- Energize.

06:37.230 --> 06:39.940
Those ammonia storms
are less than a kilometer away.

06:40.108 --> 06:43.318
Yet they do not appear
to penetrate this breathable zone.

06:43.486 --> 06:44.820
lt's like the eye of a hurricane.

06:44.987 --> 06:48.490
Commander, what is that?

06:57.041 --> 06:58.792
A door.

07:01.379 --> 07:06.133
The structure must be here,
yet we cannot see it.

07:08.177 --> 07:11.096
Enterprise,
this is Commander Riker.

07:11.264 --> 07:14.349
As your readout shows,
this is an unusual place.

07:14.517 --> 07:18.145
Completely calm, no sound,
no movement,

07:18.312 --> 07:21.314
yet a few hundred meters away,
a storm is raging.

07:21.482 --> 07:23.442
PlCARD:
Any information about the structure?

07:23.609 --> 07:24.651
Yes, sir.

07:24.819 --> 07:27.404
There is an antique revolving door.
lt could be an entrance.

07:28.614 --> 07:30.615
Revolving door?

07:31.117 --> 07:34.035
- Number One, proceed with caution.
RlKER: Yes, sir.

07:35.872 --> 07:38.290
Well, this is what we came here for.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.500
Captain, we're entering.

07:50.428 --> 07:52.929
[PEOPLE CHATTERlNG
AND CHEERlNG]

08:20.500 --> 08:23.418
Enterprise to Away Team. Come in.

08:23.586 --> 08:26.796
We're receiving no signal at all
from them, sir.

08:27.798 --> 08:30.592
Transporter Room, lock on to
the landing party. Beam them up.

08:31.802 --> 08:33.887
We've got nothing to lock on to, sir.

08:34.931 --> 08:38.350
Riker to Enterprise.
We've entered the structure.

08:39.936 --> 08:42.145
Riker to Enterprise, come in.

08:44.023 --> 08:46.233
Come in, Enterprise.

08:47.276 --> 08:48.985
When they went through
that antique doorway,

08:49.153 --> 08:50.987
the signal just disappeared, sir.

08:53.074 --> 08:54.908
What's causing the interference?

08:55.535 --> 08:56.868
Unknown.

08:57.370 --> 08:58.662
Are they receiving us?

08:59.580 --> 09:02.374
No. We're going to have
to recalibrate all the frequencies

09:02.542 --> 09:04.292
to find one that'll work.

09:04.460 --> 09:06.211
Then do it.

09:11.968 --> 09:16.638
Sir, without communication,
we should beam up immediately.

09:16.806 --> 09:20.517
We're here. There's no danger.
We'll look around, then leave.

09:20.685 --> 09:24.020
Checking in, gentlemen?
You'll have to go to the front desk.

09:24.188 --> 09:27.023
Very good. We'll start with that.

09:35.408 --> 09:37.033
[BELL DlNGS]

09:39.620 --> 09:40.704
[RlKER CLEARS THROAT]

09:42.582 --> 09:44.583
Welcome, gentlemen.

09:45.876 --> 09:47.752
Have a nice trip?

09:51.007 --> 09:52.215
Do you know us?

09:52.842 --> 09:54.634
We've been expecting you.

09:54.802 --> 09:57.846
A trio of foreign gentlemen.

09:58.014 --> 10:00.599
Yes, we're from
the United Federation of Planets.

10:01.100 --> 10:04.894
Of course you are.
Welcome to the Hotel Royale.

10:05.104 --> 10:06.521
[DOOR OPENS]

10:08.232 --> 10:09.983
Excuse me.

10:10.151 --> 10:12.569
- Did Rita call?
- l'm busy.

10:12.737 --> 10:15.947
You're busy?
This is my life l'm talking about here.

10:16.115 --> 10:18.408
Now, did Rita call or not?

10:19.744 --> 10:24.289
No. And for your own good,
you'd better quit thinking about Rita.

10:24.457 --> 10:27.292
- l'm not afraid of Mickey D.
- Then you're a fool.

10:27.460 --> 10:30.295
Anybody with any sense
is afraid of Mickey D.

10:30.463 --> 10:33.632
lf Rita calls, you let me know.

10:42.767 --> 10:44.768
The kid's just asking for trouble.

10:44.935 --> 10:46.269
Rita's too much for him to handle

10:46.437 --> 10:49.272
and Mickey D's gonna
plant his face in the pavement.

10:50.858 --> 10:53.735
Now, here are your room keys.

11:00.242 --> 11:03.036
And some complimentary
casino chips.

11:11.170 --> 11:12.879
Enjoy.

11:15.633 --> 11:17.217
What is this place?

11:17.718 --> 11:19.719
How did a being like you get here?

11:19.887 --> 11:21.888
Well, this is the Royale, of course.

11:22.056 --> 11:25.058
And my personal life is really
none of your business, thank you.

11:25.226 --> 11:27.519
What he means is,
what planet is this?

11:28.270 --> 11:31.940
- l beg your pardon?
- This planet. What do you call it?

11:32.692 --> 11:34.067
Earth.

11:34.235 --> 11:35.985
What do you call it?

11:36.153 --> 11:38.154
We call it Theta Vlll.

11:39.281 --> 11:40.907
How charming.

12:05.057 --> 12:07.475
- Commander.
- Yes, Data?

12:09.437 --> 12:12.313
None of these people
are emitting life signs.

12:12.481 --> 12:15.108
You mean, they're not alive?

12:16.026 --> 12:17.861
Then what are they?

12:30.249 --> 12:33.668
These beings, are they machines

12:33.836 --> 12:36.588
or mere illusions
designed to deceive us?

12:36.756 --> 12:39.924
Not illusion, lieutenant.
They do exist.

12:40.092 --> 12:43.595
But they do not register
as either man or machine.

12:44.972 --> 12:47.390
Take this creature, for example.

12:47.850 --> 12:51.060
He does not exhibit
any DNA structure.

12:51.604 --> 12:55.023
Excuse me, son. Look who's talking.

12:55.191 --> 12:58.401
Man, you sound just like my ex-wife.

12:59.779 --> 13:03.782
All right,
time to get down to business.

13:05.201 --> 13:09.037
What sort of business
do you suppose he is getting down to?

13:19.799 --> 13:20.924
Status report?

13:21.091 --> 13:24.302
We're attempting
to employ alternate encoding schemes.

13:24.470 --> 13:27.472
Yeah, there could be hundreds
of possible combinations.

13:29.225 --> 13:32.310
ls there an intelligence
causing this interference?

13:32.478 --> 13:36.314
Hmm.
That's impossible to tell, captain.

13:48.661 --> 13:52.872
lt's unlike Commander Riker
not to follow procedure.

13:53.541 --> 13:55.124
When he lost contact
with the Enterprise,

13:55.292 --> 13:58.628
he should have returned immediately
to the beam-down coordinates.

13:58.796 --> 14:01.798
l don't feel he's in any danger.

14:01.966 --> 14:05.218
ln fact, if l could choose one word
to assess his mood,

14:05.386 --> 14:07.804
it would be amused.

14:09.098 --> 14:10.849
Amused?

14:12.601 --> 14:14.060
[PlCARD SlGHS]

14:16.856 --> 14:20.483
We want some chips here, mister.
Yes, sirree. Ha, ha.

14:22.486 --> 14:24.487
- You're new around here, aren't you?
- Yes, sir.

14:24.655 --> 14:27.782
Sit down. l'm gonna teach you
how this game is played, boy.

14:27.950 --> 14:29.826
[TEXAS CHUCKLlNG]

14:30.870 --> 14:32.787
Go ahead, ante up.

14:33.455 --> 14:35.206
Oh, me.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.418
He wants you to cut the cards.

14:38.586 --> 14:41.838
- Ah. ls this poker?
- No, no. Blackjack.

14:43.215 --> 14:46.050
Blackjack? Accessing.

14:47.887 --> 14:50.430
Ah. Also known as Twenty-one.

14:50.598 --> 14:52.765
The number which defines
the object of the game.

14:52.933 --> 14:56.477
Picture cards are worth ten,
aces one or eleven,

14:56.645 --> 14:59.147
all other cards face value.

14:59.315 --> 15:02.317
Boy, you're right. You are right.

15:05.529 --> 15:06.696
[WHlSTLES]

15:06.864 --> 15:08.615
TEXAS:
Pretty smooth.

15:09.325 --> 15:10.366
Run them, boy.

15:10.534 --> 15:12.744
Make them nice
because there's no bread in the house.

15:18.417 --> 15:21.419
- Twenty-one, twenty-one, twenty-one.
- Look at your hand, honey.

15:21.587 --> 15:24.422
That gal has got to win.

15:25.257 --> 15:29.344
Now, honey, you got 1 5
and the dealer's showing ten.

15:30.346 --> 15:32.221
Do l hit, Texas, or do l stand?

15:32.389 --> 15:35.725
lf you've got to win, you've got to hit.

15:36.435 --> 15:37.477
Hit me.

15:38.938 --> 15:43.107
- Oh. Damn.
- Aw. Shoot.

15:43.275 --> 15:44.317
Hit me.

15:46.570 --> 15:50.156
Twenty-one. And a winner.
Yes, sirree. Ha, ha.

15:50.783 --> 15:52.241
Hit me.

15:53.369 --> 15:54.661
Another, please.

15:54.828 --> 15:56.371
Don't you think you've had
about enough?

15:57.164 --> 16:01.376
lf the objective of the game
is to approach a total of 21 points,

16:01.543 --> 16:03.586
l will definitely need another card.

16:03.754 --> 16:06.756
- Yeah.
- Boy, you have got the brass.

16:06.924 --> 16:09.676
Do you know what the odds
are on a five-card Charlie?

16:09.843 --> 16:12.845
Hell, you're just throwing
your money away.

16:13.597 --> 16:14.889
Hit me.

16:16.809 --> 16:18.726
TEXAS: How'd you...?
VANESSA: Whoo!

16:18.894 --> 16:21.062
TEXAS:
Shut my mouth.

16:22.898 --> 16:26.317
Hey, you're not one of them
card-counting fellas, are you?

16:27.319 --> 16:31.322
The number of the cards
and their values remain quite constant.

16:31.490 --> 16:33.366
What would be the purpose
in counting them?

16:34.618 --> 16:36.869
- Yeah.
RlKER: You having fun, Data?

16:38.205 --> 16:39.831
Fun, sir?

16:39.999 --> 16:42.125
While there is a certain amount
of enjoyment involved,

16:42.292 --> 16:43.918
l am mainly conducting research
into the--

16:44.086 --> 16:46.254
- Save it. We're getting out of here.
- Understood, sir.

16:46.422 --> 16:47.964
TEXAS:
You guys are holding up the game.

16:48.132 --> 16:49.382
Our apologies, sir.

16:50.134 --> 16:51.467
l'll watch your chips.

16:52.136 --> 16:55.346
- Ah. Thank you, sir.
TEXAS: Hey.

16:55.931 --> 16:56.973
The hat.

16:59.643 --> 17:01.269
Sorry, sir.

17:02.646 --> 17:03.730
Deal them up.

17:09.611 --> 17:10.653
Progress.

17:10.821 --> 17:13.322
We've accessed the range
of encoding scheme alternates.

17:13.490 --> 17:17.702
The difficulty is in the frequency range.
And interference is highly variable.

17:17.870 --> 17:18.911
See, the problem may be

17:19.079 --> 17:20.872
with the envelope
covering the structure.

17:21.040 --> 17:24.042
There are hydrogen carbon helix
patterns throughout.

17:24.209 --> 17:25.960
Any transmissions
are simply scattered

17:26.128 --> 17:27.420
and refracted at random.

17:27.588 --> 17:30.423
- No wonder you can't get through.
- Exactly.

17:32.760 --> 17:35.511
PlCARD: Those are some fairly
aggressive computations, lieutenant.

17:35.679 --> 17:40.308
l'm comparing the molecular integrity
of that bubble against our phasers.

17:41.393 --> 17:43.394
- ls penetration possible?
- l don't know just yet.

17:43.562 --> 17:45.063
lt may be an option.

17:45.230 --> 17:48.858
- l'd like to run this test.
- Make it so.

18:12.341 --> 18:14.092
Try that again.

18:29.149 --> 18:31.359
Let's find another way out of here.

18:37.116 --> 18:44.330
Excuse me.

18:44.498 --> 18:47.416
Aside from the main door,
is there another exit l might use?

18:47.584 --> 18:49.544
[SLOT MACHlNE RlNGlNG]

18:51.755 --> 18:53.506
Excuse--

18:56.969 --> 18:58.678
Excuse me.

19:01.765 --> 19:04.767
Say, l was wondering
if you could tell me...

19:21.034 --> 19:22.952
[GRUNTlNG]

19:28.584 --> 19:31.002
That's a good deal
of structural integrity, Worf.

19:31.170 --> 19:33.796
- Permission to use phaser, sir.
- Granted.

19:58.822 --> 20:03.659
Sir, l can find no other exits.
l believe we are trapped here.

20:09.249 --> 20:11.125
PlCARD:
Captain's log, supplemental.

20:11.293 --> 20:13.920
We remain in orbit
around Theta Vlll,

20:14.087 --> 20:16.839
still out of contact
with the away team.

20:17.424 --> 20:18.549
We're almost there, captain.

20:18.717 --> 20:21.719
We'll be able to attempt contact
in a few minutes.

20:24.389 --> 20:27.600
Captain, the situation down there
has changed.

20:28.477 --> 20:29.894
ln what way?

20:30.062 --> 20:33.940
Commander Riker
has become tense,

20:34.107 --> 20:35.149
closed in.

20:35.317 --> 20:37.068
He's feeling trapped.

20:44.660 --> 20:47.161
Phasers are totally ineffective
on all surfaces.

20:47.329 --> 20:49.956
- Sir, our options appear quite limited.
- We don't have any.

20:50.123 --> 20:53.084
lf we're going to get out of here, we're
going to have to do it on our own.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.628
l'm gonna get some answers
out of that desk clerk.

21:04.096 --> 21:06.305
- Are you crazy?
- Wrong.

21:06.473 --> 21:08.140
l'm finally getting some smarts.

21:08.308 --> 21:10.518
Do you think you're gonna scare
Mickey D with that gun?

21:10.686 --> 21:12.687
l'm gonna make him leave
Rita alone.

21:12.854 --> 21:16.482
Kid, she's a big girl.
And she's Mickey D's girl.

21:16.650 --> 21:19.652
Not anymore. Not after tonight.

21:19.820 --> 21:22.822
Look, kid, l like you.
l don't wanna see you get hurt.

21:22.990 --> 21:26.617
- Especially over some dame.
- Don't call her that.

21:26.785 --> 21:27.994
You'll see.

21:28.161 --> 21:32.373
You'll see how tough Mickey D is.
He's nothing.

21:34.293 --> 21:36.168
[SUPERVlSOR SlGHS]

21:37.713 --> 21:40.256
- l want some answers.
- l'm sure the concierge will be glad--

21:40.424 --> 21:42.341
We would like
to get out of here now.

21:42.509 --> 21:44.427
The Royale's exits
are clearly marked.

21:44.594 --> 21:45.928
That's not good enough.

21:46.096 --> 21:48.306
lf you have a complaint
about the service you've received

21:48.473 --> 21:51.309
during your stay here, you can always
take it up with the manager.

21:51.476 --> 21:53.311
Fine.
l'd like to see him immediately.

21:53.478 --> 21:56.480
l'm afraid the manager
is very busy.

22:03.155 --> 22:05.239
PlCARD [OVER COM, DlSTORTED]:
Riker, can you read?

22:05.407 --> 22:06.449
Yes.

22:06.616 --> 22:10.619
There's a good deal of interference,
captain, but you are getting through.

22:11.955 --> 22:14.248
Number One,
why haven't you left that building?

22:14.833 --> 22:16.959
We tried, sir.
lt seems like we're trapped in here.

22:17.127 --> 22:19.920
We're in no immediate danger.
But l am concerned.

22:20.088 --> 22:23.090
Something about your location
is interfering with communication.

22:23.258 --> 22:26.677
- We are working on the problem.
RIKER: Standing by, sir.

22:26.845 --> 22:28.429
Captain, these frequencies
are unstable.

22:28.597 --> 22:30.806
- Then find others.
- Yes, sir.

22:34.561 --> 22:36.854
What is going on down there?

22:43.653 --> 22:45.279
DATA:
Commander.

22:46.615 --> 22:48.282
l am picking up
something most unusual

22:48.450 --> 22:50.659
in another section of this structure.

22:50.827 --> 22:53.579
- lt appears to be human DNA.
- Where?

22:53.747 --> 22:57.750
Thirty-one-point-nine meters above
and to the right of us.

22:58.668 --> 23:01.670
Perhaps those turbolifts
could take us there.

23:08.220 --> 23:10.846
Seems to be malfunctioning.

23:12.933 --> 23:14.725
[ELEVATOR DlNGS]

23:34.413 --> 23:37.623
The reading l received
is from behind this door, sir.

23:56.935 --> 23:59.562
My reading is intensifying, sir.

24:00.605 --> 24:02.314
RlKER:
Are you getting any life signs?

24:02.858 --> 24:04.442
None, sir.

24:20.459 --> 24:23.419
Definitely human. Male.

24:23.587 --> 24:26.046
Looks like the poor devil
died in his sleep.

24:27.674 --> 24:30.092
WORF:
What a terrible way to die.

24:31.470 --> 24:34.597
He has been dead for 283 years, sir.

24:34.764 --> 24:37.308
The lack
of any advanced decomposition

24:37.476 --> 24:39.768
is due to the sterile environment.

24:39.936 --> 24:42.271
Why would anyone go
to all this trouble?

24:42.439 --> 24:44.773
lt's just window dressing
for a dead man.

24:44.941 --> 24:46.317
WORF:
Commander.

24:49.070 --> 24:51.405
ls this significant, sir?

24:53.033 --> 24:54.116
American.

24:55.535 --> 24:57.119
DATA:
Fifty-two stars, sir.

24:57.287 --> 25:01.040
Places it
between 2033 and 2079 AD.

25:01.208 --> 25:03.834
Correlates with the debris we found.

25:08.381 --> 25:10.591
Colonel S. Richey.

25:13.261 --> 25:15.471
Rest in peace, colonel.

25:18.350 --> 25:20.059
PlCARD [OVER COM]:
Picard to Riker.

25:20.227 --> 25:21.268
Finally.

25:21.436 --> 25:24.188
Riker. Go ahead.
You're coming through clearly now.

25:24.356 --> 25:25.981
What's your situation?

25:26.149 --> 25:29.568
Well, this structure was apparently
made to resemble 20th century Earth.

25:29.736 --> 25:31.737
All attempts to exit have failed.

25:31.905 --> 25:34.156
PlCARD: We haven't found a way
to transport you back yet.

25:34.324 --> 25:35.366
l assumed as much, sir.

25:35.534 --> 25:37.618
We've also located the remains
of a human.

25:37.786 --> 25:39.828
Request identity scan.

25:39.996 --> 25:43.207
Colonel Richey, American,
first initial S,

25:43.375 --> 25:44.917
roughly the same time period.

25:45.085 --> 25:46.710
Do it.

25:48.129 --> 25:51.966
Commander, some curiosities.

25:53.552 --> 25:54.718
Books.

25:54.886 --> 25:56.095
A novel.

25:56.263 --> 25:59.890
Hotel Royale? Summarize, please.

26:03.270 --> 26:05.688
lnformation retrieved, captain.

26:06.606 --> 26:08.440
- Number One?
RlKER: Go ahead, captain.

26:08.608 --> 26:11.026
We have the information
you requested.

26:11.194 --> 26:13.821
Colonel Stephen Richey
was the commanding officer

26:13.989 --> 26:16.073
of the explorer ship Charybdis,

26:16.241 --> 26:21.370
which had a terrestrial launch date
of July 23rd, 2037.

26:21.538 --> 26:23.330
lt was the third manned attempt

26:23.498 --> 26:26.542
to travel beyond the confines
of Earth's solar system.

26:26.710 --> 26:30.337
lts telemetry failed.
lt was never heard from again.

26:31.214 --> 26:34.883
Do you believe that you've discovered
the remains of Colonel Richey?

26:35.051 --> 26:36.719
Yes. And, captain,
we found something else.

26:36.886 --> 26:39.138
A novel by Todd Matthews

26:39.306 --> 26:42.141
entitled Hotel Royale,
which is the name of this structure.

26:42.309 --> 26:43.392
Data.

26:43.560 --> 26:47.187
Captain, this is the story of a group
of compulsive gamblers

26:47.355 --> 26:50.065
caught up in a web of crime,
corruption and deceit.

26:50.233 --> 26:53.068
lt is told by a nefarious lothario,
Mickey D,

26:53.236 --> 26:55.446
who appears only at the climax
of the story

26:55.614 --> 26:58.991
to carry out the cold-blooded murder
of the hotel bellboy.

26:59.159 --> 27:01.368
There is also a sub-plot
about an older man

27:01.536 --> 27:04.538
conspiring with a younger woman
to murder her husband.

27:04.706 --> 27:06.540
She is squandering her inheritance.

27:06.708 --> 27:09.126
Captain, this novel
and everything Data just described

27:09.294 --> 27:12.504
seems to be exactly
what's happening at this hotel.

27:13.465 --> 27:14.506
Extraordinary.

27:14.674 --> 27:17.384
RlKER: There's also one other thing,
a diary, with only one entry.

27:17.552 --> 27:19.928
Obviously made by Colonel Richey.

27:20.096 --> 27:22.514
PICARD: Can you read it?
- Yes.

27:22.682 --> 27:24.099
"l write this in the hope

27:24.267 --> 27:26.727
that it will someday be read
by human eyes.

27:26.895 --> 27:30.105
l can only surmise at this point,
but apparently our exploratory shuttle

27:30.273 --> 27:32.691
was contaminated
by an alien life-form

27:32.859 --> 27:36.278
which infected and killed all personnel
except myself.

27:36.446 --> 27:40.449
l awakened to find myself
here in the Royale Hotel,

27:40.617 --> 27:43.577
precisely as described
in the novel I found in my room.

27:44.287 --> 27:48.624
And for the last 38 years
l have survived here.

27:48.792 --> 27:50.542
l have come to understand

27:50.710 --> 27:53.295
that the alien contaminators
created this place for me

27:53.463 --> 27:55.422
out of some sense of guilt.

27:55.965 --> 27:57.966
Presuming that the novel
we had onboard the shuttle

27:58.134 --> 28:00.761
about the Hotel Royale
was in fact a guide

28:00.929 --> 28:05.265
to our preferred lifestyle
and social habits.

28:05.684 --> 28:08.811
Obviously, they thought
this was the world from which l came.

28:08.978 --> 28:10.979
l hold no malice
toward my benefactors.

28:11.147 --> 28:14.191
They could not possibly know the hell
that they have put me through.

28:14.359 --> 28:16.902
For it was such a badly
written book,

28:17.070 --> 28:20.698
filled with endless clichÃ©
and shallow characters.

28:21.908 --> 28:24.743
l shall welcome death
when it comes."

28:30.041 --> 28:32.334
l understand, Number One.

28:32.752 --> 28:35.754
Now we know why all that is there.

28:36.214 --> 28:38.632
Why can't you get out?

28:46.641 --> 28:48.225
- Number One?
RlKER [OVER COM]: Yes, sir?

28:48.393 --> 28:49.935
Lieutenant La Forge has a thought.

28:50.103 --> 28:54.690
He believes we can phaser a slice
in the field surrounding the structure.

28:54.858 --> 28:57.693
That means the atmosphere
of the planet would instantly rush in.

28:57.861 --> 29:01.530
Our projected survival
would be approximately 12 seconds.

29:01.698 --> 29:05.576
Correct. The cryogenic process
would be nearly instantaneous.

29:05.744 --> 29:07.411
RlKER:
But I assume you could revive us.

29:07.579 --> 29:10.205
Yes. ln theory.

29:10.373 --> 29:12.499
PlCARD:
You must understand, Number One.

29:12.667 --> 29:14.793
We'll wait here for months
if necessary.

29:14.961 --> 29:17.588
We're just considering options.

29:17.756 --> 29:20.257
lf you're trying to motivate us
to find our own way out of here,

29:20.425 --> 29:21.842
you've succeeded, captain.

29:22.010 --> 29:23.802
[PHONE RlNGlNG]

29:40.987 --> 29:42.613
Yes?

29:46.409 --> 29:49.912
There is a female voice asking
if we want room service.

29:54.000 --> 29:56.627
l believe she is asking
if we want the room cleaned.

29:56.795 --> 29:58.128
Tell her no.

29:58.838 --> 30:00.422
No.

30:04.636 --> 30:05.719
What did she say?

30:06.554 --> 30:10.641
She said the kitchen will be open
24 hours if we change our minds.

30:12.101 --> 30:13.852
We're going to explore the rest
of the hotel.

30:14.020 --> 30:16.063
We'll keep a com line open.
You go down to the lobby.

30:16.231 --> 30:18.273
See if there's anything we've missed.
Talk to guests.

30:18.441 --> 30:22.152
Try to find out who or what they are.
l'll check out the rest of the floors.

30:38.169 --> 30:40.379
Computer, locate and display,

30:40.547 --> 30:45.801
the text of the novel entitled
Hotel Royale by Todd Matthews.

30:45.969 --> 30:47.594
COMPUTER:
Accessing.

30:48.680 --> 30:50.931
lf the cause of the difficulties
is in the novel,

30:51.099 --> 30:54.101
we may find the solution
within its pages.

30:55.562 --> 31:00.274
Ah. "lt was a dark and stormy night."

31:00.525 --> 31:01.984
[PlCARD SlGHS]

31:02.151 --> 31:04.152
lt's not a promising beginning.

31:04.320 --> 31:06.154
May get better.

31:17.709 --> 31:20.377
l suggest we separate
and blend in with these beings.

31:20.545 --> 31:23.297
Casual queries
offered inconspicuously

31:23.464 --> 31:25.299
might prove fruitful.

31:37.979 --> 31:40.814
VANESSA:
l need a four. Give me a four.

31:41.232 --> 31:43.525
Oh, shoot. Heh.

31:43.693 --> 31:45.527
How much do l have left here?

31:45.695 --> 31:48.530
Honey, now, you know it's bad luck
to count your chips at the table.

31:48.698 --> 31:50.824
- Yeah?
- Excuse me, sir.

31:50.992 --> 31:53.869
Might l inquire, where are you from?

31:54.037 --> 31:56.038
Lubbock, Texas.

31:56.456 --> 31:58.665
And how did you get here?

31:59.125 --> 32:01.126
To Vegas? Drove my car.

32:01.294 --> 32:03.837
l got a '91 Caddy
with only 80,000 miles on her.

32:04.422 --> 32:07.633
- Where is your automobile now?
- Out front, l suppose.

32:07.800 --> 32:09.635
What the hell difference
does it make?

32:10.345 --> 32:13.430
- Could you take me there?
VANESSA: Hit me.

32:14.766 --> 32:16.558
l'm losing my shirt.

32:17.769 --> 32:19.686
TEXAS:
Son, why would l want to do that?

32:20.355 --> 32:23.315
Can't you see l'm trying
to help this little lady?

32:24.150 --> 32:28.445
l believe you are trapped
inside the Royale, just as l am.

32:28.613 --> 32:31.031
Sure does seem that way
when you're losing, don't it?

32:31.199 --> 32:33.408
We're just trying
to turn this lady's wagon around

32:33.576 --> 32:35.577
and win back some lost change.

32:35.745 --> 32:37.329
Otherwise,
she's in a desperate situation

32:37.497 --> 32:39.623
and she's got nowhere to turn.

32:39.791 --> 32:43.210
Well, almost nowhere.

32:45.922 --> 32:49.508
- l stay, right?
- l wouldn't.

32:50.885 --> 32:52.761
The odds favor standing pat.

32:55.848 --> 32:57.057
What do l do?

33:00.395 --> 33:02.104
Do you want a card or not?

33:05.400 --> 33:06.942
Hit me.

33:07.485 --> 33:09.653
Oh, too many.

33:09.862 --> 33:11.154
Oh.

33:12.073 --> 33:13.949
l've almost lost it all.

33:14.117 --> 33:19.329
- What am l gonna do?
- There, there, there, there.

33:30.008 --> 33:32.426
- What did you find?
- Nothing.

33:32.593 --> 33:35.053
SUPERVlSOR: Kid, Rita just called.
- She did? What did she say?

33:35.221 --> 33:37.389
lt was kind of hard to tell.
She was crying.

33:37.557 --> 33:39.266
Crying? Damn.

33:39.434 --> 33:42.060
Mickey D thinks he can treat people
any way he wants.

33:42.228 --> 33:44.229
Well, that's all over now.

34:06.252 --> 34:08.170
You were told.

34:08.337 --> 34:11.423
lt's not for you to make the call.
lt's for Rita.

34:12.258 --> 34:14.634
Well, she sent me to tell you.

34:14.802 --> 34:18.055
Okay, boys, look, we can't afford
to have any trouble in here.

34:18.222 --> 34:20.223
Why don't you
just take this outside?

34:20.391 --> 34:23.226
Yeah. l like that.

34:23.394 --> 34:25.270
Come on, baggage man.

34:25.438 --> 34:28.065
MlCKEY D [OVER COM]:
Let's you and me take it outside.

34:28.232 --> 34:30.692
BELLBOY: When I was a kid,
I used to look up to you guys.

34:30.860 --> 34:34.488
The suit, the fancy shoes.

34:34.655 --> 34:37.657
I really thought
that made you somebody.

34:37.825 --> 34:39.409
But you're nobody.

34:39.577 --> 34:41.912
[VOLUME DECREASES] She could
make something out of her life.

34:42.080 --> 34:45.582
l don't believe this dialogue.
Did humans really talk like that?

34:45.750 --> 34:47.167
Not in real life.

34:47.335 --> 34:49.544
Remember, everything
that's going on down there

34:49.712 --> 34:54.132
is taken from what Colonel Richey
calls a second-rate novel.

34:56.094 --> 34:57.928
BELLBOY:
She could do something with her life.

34:58.096 --> 35:00.347
- If she only had the chance.
- With your permission, sir.

35:00.515 --> 35:02.516
MlCKEY D:
She's somebody. She's my girl.

35:02.683 --> 35:04.309
BELLBOY:
You got her on the stuff.

35:04.477 --> 35:07.521
The only reason she stays with you
is because you feed her sickness.

35:08.064 --> 35:09.815
You gotta let me help her.

35:12.443 --> 35:15.362
Well, why don't we just go outside
and talk about it?

35:16.948 --> 35:20.617
- Just watch yourself.
- Don't worry.

35:27.125 --> 35:30.752
lt's all part of the novel.
Don't interfere.

35:37.218 --> 35:38.426
[ALL SHRlEK]

35:57.363 --> 35:59.781
You should have listened to me, kid.

36:00.158 --> 36:02.701
No woman's worth dying for.

36:03.494 --> 36:05.245
Killing for,

36:06.038 --> 36:07.664
not dying for.

36:27.185 --> 36:30.187
- Riker to Enterprise.
- Yes, Number One?

36:30.354 --> 36:32.480
RlKER:
A bizarre incident just took place.

36:32.648 --> 36:35.901
The shoot-out between the bellboy
and Mickey D.

36:36.068 --> 36:39.237
Yes, and Mickey D just walked
out the door. How did he do that?

36:42.200 --> 36:44.451
lt's on page 244.

36:45.203 --> 36:47.954
The novel, right. How does it end?

36:49.290 --> 36:52.125
A bad love affair
ends in a bloody shoot-out,

36:52.293 --> 36:56.296
the hotel gets bought out
and life goes on.

36:56.464 --> 36:57.923
Such as it is.

36:58.090 --> 37:00.258
The hotel gets bought? By whom?

37:04.055 --> 37:05.305
lsn't specific.

37:05.473 --> 37:07.057
Simply refers to foreign investors.

37:07.225 --> 37:11.269
Sale price, 1 2.5 million
United States dollars.

37:11.437 --> 37:12.604
They return home,

37:12.772 --> 37:15.857
leaving the assistant manager
in charge.

37:19.487 --> 37:20.904
Captain.

37:22.949 --> 37:25.033
That's how we're getting out.

37:26.244 --> 37:28.662
We're buying this place.

37:36.671 --> 37:38.797
lt is all a question of probabilities.

37:38.965 --> 37:41.675
Quite simple, really, if one bets
with any sequential consistency.

37:41.842 --> 37:42.884
Elaborate.

37:43.552 --> 37:45.387
The combinations totaling
seven or 1 1

37:45.554 --> 37:48.765
have considerable value
when achieved on the primary attempt.

37:48.933 --> 37:51.559
With eight variations possible
to create those totals,

37:51.727 --> 37:54.062
the likelihood of those totals occurring
is not significant.

37:54.230 --> 37:56.439
- However--
- Okay, okay. Can you do it?

37:56.607 --> 37:58.608
l believe so, sir.

38:03.155 --> 38:04.197
Eight's the point.

38:04.365 --> 38:07.701
Eighter from Decatur,
County Seat of Wise. Do it, do it.

38:10.371 --> 38:11.621
Aw, snake eyes.

38:11.789 --> 38:15.375
Single digits on each cube
are not at all desirable.

38:15.543 --> 38:19.296
- You're almost broke.
- Relax, honey, it's only money.

38:19.463 --> 38:22.048
Yeah, but if you lose it all,
l won't even have a place to sleep.

38:22.216 --> 38:24.134
Don't you worry your little head,
honey.

38:24.302 --> 38:26.511
l'd never let that happen.

38:32.143 --> 38:34.561
Go, baby, let's go. Here they come,
here they come, baby.

38:34.729 --> 38:36.354
CROUPlER: Seven.
TEXAS: Ah.

38:38.983 --> 38:41.401
- Your turn, slick.
- Go to work.

38:41.569 --> 38:44.404
Maybe this turkey
will bring us some luck.

38:55.333 --> 38:56.750
Six. Six is your number.

38:56.917 --> 38:59.419
Hell, my blind grandma
can make a six, boy.

38:59.587 --> 39:01.379
Come on, roll them.

39:01.547 --> 39:03.548
l thought seven and 1 1 had value.

39:03.716 --> 39:05.550
Actually, six is a valid point.

39:05.718 --> 39:06.926
Of course now the objective

39:07.094 --> 39:09.763
is to roll a duplicate six
before hitting seven.

39:09.930 --> 39:13.183
But the probability of making a six is
no greater than that of rolling a seven.

39:14.268 --> 39:17.103
There is a certain degree
of random fortune involved.

39:17.271 --> 39:19.397
l believe that is why
they call it gambling.

39:20.066 --> 39:21.399
Yeah.

39:25.988 --> 39:28.198
CROUPlER:
Seven. Seven away. Next shooter.

39:28.366 --> 39:32.369
- So much for your new turkey.
- Give Slick another shot.

39:32.536 --> 39:35.163
l got a feeling about you, boy.

39:38.542 --> 39:41.669
Commander, these cubes
are improperly balanced.

39:41.837 --> 39:43.755
l believe their final resting
position would be--

39:43.923 --> 39:45.131
Can you repair them?

39:46.509 --> 39:47.550
l believe so.

39:50.054 --> 39:52.263
l will make another attempt.

39:55.684 --> 39:58.103
Baby needs a new pair of shoes.

40:00.439 --> 40:01.856
Eleven! Atta boy!

40:02.024 --> 40:05.652
Do that a few more times,
we're all gonna get well. Ha, ha.

40:09.407 --> 40:12.617
- Seven and winner.
- And another one! Ha-ha-ha.

40:14.245 --> 40:16.663
Keep going, boy.
We've got him hot now. Let's go.

40:16.831 --> 40:20.667
RlKER: Double them up. Here we go.
- Keep rolling, boy, keep rolling.

40:22.044 --> 40:24.254
TEXAS:
Seven, a winner!

40:28.926 --> 40:30.510
Status, Number One?

40:31.637 --> 40:33.638
We're having a nice run of luck,
captain.

40:33.806 --> 40:35.598
PICARD: Don't get out of character,
commander.

40:35.766 --> 40:36.975
Sir?

40:37.143 --> 40:42.647
The foreign investors in the book are
described as flamboyantly generous.

40:44.442 --> 40:46.067
Yes, sir. l understand.

40:47.695 --> 40:49.904
MAN:
One more time. One more time.

40:51.532 --> 40:52.699
TEXAS: Hey!
VANESSA: Whoo-hoo!

40:52.867 --> 40:54.617
Seven. Look at that. Ha, ha.

40:54.785 --> 40:57.120
Tex, darling.

40:57.288 --> 40:59.164
- You're brilliant.
- Yeah.

40:59.331 --> 41:00.790
And l'm good-looking too.

41:00.958 --> 41:02.333
[TEXAS LAUGHS]

41:03.127 --> 41:05.962
- lsn't that enough?
- No. Don't wanna come up short.

41:06.130 --> 41:09.799
- You are keeping count?
- Yes, sir. 1 2.3 million.

41:09.967 --> 41:13.261
Perhaps l will bet 700,000.

41:13.721 --> 41:15.472
No, bet it all.

41:15.639 --> 41:18.850
But, sir, the sale price of this edifice
is 1 2.5 million.

41:19.018 --> 41:21.102
We need some spreading
around money, Data.

41:21.604 --> 41:23.313
- Sir?
- Bet it all.

41:23.481 --> 41:26.691
Here you go.
A little something for you, Ziggy.

41:26.859 --> 41:28.860
A little something
for those cocktail waitresses.

41:29.028 --> 41:31.696
You run this outside
and give it to the parking lot attendant.

41:31.864 --> 41:32.947
You're very kind, sir.

41:33.699 --> 41:35.825
Here you go, Vanessa.
A little something for you too.

41:35.993 --> 41:37.285
Thank you.

41:37.453 --> 41:40.288
When the train comes in,
everybody rides.

41:40.456 --> 41:42.874
Yeah, and l'm getting off
at this station.

41:43.042 --> 41:48.046
After 1 8 passes, air gets a little too thin
for this country boy.

41:48.214 --> 41:51.341
- l'm betting against you, fella.
- Are you nuts?

41:51.509 --> 41:53.718
l do not believe
that is a prudent choice, sir.

41:53.886 --> 41:58.389
Hey, that's what horse racing's about.
Roll them, boy.

42:12.947 --> 42:14.405
CROUPlER:
Seven. Seven a winner.

42:14.573 --> 42:16.074
[PEOPLE CHEER]

42:17.576 --> 42:19.118
The man has the touch.

42:21.372 --> 42:24.207
You knew you were gonna throw
that seven, didn't you?

42:24.375 --> 42:26.626
You just let me go down the tubes.

42:27.753 --> 42:29.420
l tried to caution you, sir.

42:29.964 --> 42:33.591
What was it?
l mean, was it personal, or what?

42:33.759 --> 42:35.969
Because l didn't show you my car?

42:37.304 --> 42:39.138
Now.

42:39.306 --> 42:41.140
l wish to cash in, sir.

42:41.767 --> 42:43.851
l'm afraid you've broken the bank.

42:44.019 --> 42:47.105
Just take 1 2.5 million,
the purchase price of this hotel.

42:47.273 --> 42:48.856
Spread the rest around.

42:52.069 --> 42:56.072
- You're the foreign investors.
- That's right.

42:56.240 --> 42:59.450
We just bought this place lock,
stock and barrel.

42:59.618 --> 43:01.536
Consider it a done deal.

43:01.704 --> 43:04.914
l like you fellas. You got style.

43:05.082 --> 43:06.958
Let me buy you guys a drink.

43:07.126 --> 43:08.710
Just enjoy the game.

43:08.877 --> 43:10.712
Don't let them change the dice
on you.

43:10.879 --> 43:12.505
TEXAS:
You got it.

43:30.316 --> 43:33.776
Enterprise, this is the away team.
We're clear of the structure.

